♪ And I ain't going back ♪

04:03.743 --> 04:06.913
♪ My heart is here to stay ♪

04:06.955 --> 04:08.957
♪ Oh oh ♪

04:31.312 --> 04:33.231
(sighing)

04:33.273 --> 04:34.190
Hello?

04:45.827 --> 04:46.786
Where's your stuff?

04:47.620 --> 04:48.496
I travel light.

04:49.956 --> 04:51.583
You're not packed, are you?

04:51.624 --> 04:52.625
I thought it was tomorrow.

04:52.667 --> 04:53.835
You could at least have called

04:53.877 --> 04:54.753
or left a message.

04:54.794 --> 04:56.629
Hey Robbie.

04:56.671 --> 04:58.131
Have you seen my jacket?

04:58.173 --> 04:59.007
Oh.

05:00.008 --> 05:01.426
Hi.

05:01.468 --> 05:04.095
Yeah, Jessica, this is
my son, actually, Jack.

05:04.137 --> 05:06.514
Jack, this is Jessica.

05:06.556 --> 05:07.390
Hi, Jessica.

05:08.892 --> 05:09.726
Fuck you.

05:11.644 --> 05:12.479
Jessica.

05:14.064 --> 05:15.523
Jessica.

05:15.565 --> 05:16.649
Jennifer?

05:16.691 --> 05:18.151
Jennifer, Jennifer, shit.

05:18.985 --> 05:20.195
Okay, tea.

05:20.236 --> 05:21.029
I'll make the tea.

05:21.071 --> 05:22.238
You go pack.

05:23.198 --> 05:25.825
(cars honking)

05:40.173 --> 05:42.884
Are you gonna read
the whole way there?

05:42.926 --> 05:46.012
The Dover road is famously
the most boring drive

05:46.054 --> 05:47.639
in the British Isles.

05:47.681 --> 05:48.515
Ask anyone.

05:50.016 --> 05:52.686
So you're not gonna
talk to me then.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.814
What would you
like to talk about?

05:55.855 --> 05:59.025
I don't know, the
usual father-son stuff?

06:03.863 --> 06:06.199
What are your views
on Hentai manga?

06:06.241 --> 06:08.535
Do you see it as
art or pornography?

06:11.705 --> 06:13.164
I meant like how's work.

06:13.206 --> 06:16.042
Oh, I see, an off
the peg conversation.

06:16.960 --> 06:18.753
Ah, how's work?

06:19.963 --> 06:21.172
Forget it, read your book.

06:21.214 --> 06:23.425
No, no, this is starting
to get really good.

06:24.259 --> 06:25.260
Are you eating well?

06:27.053 --> 06:30.223
Did you see the game last night?

06:30.265 --> 06:31.349
What game?

06:31.391 --> 06:33.059
You know, the one with the ball.

06:37.147 --> 06:37.981
How's Ruth?

06:40.066 --> 06:40.900
She's great.

06:41.901 --> 06:42.819
Sends you her love.

06:45.238 --> 06:46.072
Terrific.

06:49.409 --> 06:51.911
(light music)

07:04.591 --> 07:05.717
Okay, what's bugging you?

07:05.759 --> 07:06.593
Spit it out.

07:07.677 --> 07:08.887
I'm worried the house
won't be the way

07:08.928 --> 07:09.929
you remember it.

07:11.681 --> 07:12.515
Why not?

07:14.434 --> 07:16.644
You haven't been back
since you were seven.

07:17.687 --> 07:19.481
I mean the walls, for example.

07:19.522 --> 07:23.276
The walls haven't been
painted in decades.

07:23.318 --> 07:24.235
That's an easy fix.

07:24.277 --> 07:27.572
The grounds might need tending.

07:27.614 --> 07:29.949
Look, I'm not expecting Xanadu.

07:29.991 --> 07:32.952
We just cheer the place
up a bit and get it sold.

07:32.994 --> 07:33.828
Why the rush?

07:34.996 --> 07:36.831
I don't hear from
you for months,

07:36.873 --> 07:39.084
and then this sudden need
to sell the Tuscan house

07:39.125 --> 07:40.460
by last Tuesday.

07:41.461 --> 07:44.464
The house that's been
basically empty for 20 years?

07:45.632 --> 07:46.925
Look on the bright side.

07:46.966 --> 07:49.010
You'll be home on
Saturday with a big check

07:49.052 --> 07:50.762
and you can blow
your half picking up

07:50.804 --> 07:52.430
stray women in bars.

07:52.472 --> 07:54.516
Don't make assumptions
about my current lifestyle

07:54.557 --> 07:55.475
based on Jessica.

07:55.517 --> 07:56.309
Jennifer.

07:56.351 --> 07:57.185
Jennifer, fuck.

07:58.061 --> 07:59.104
Jack.

07:59.145 --> 08:01.022
My point is we
should take a moment.

08:01.064 --> 08:02.524
Look.

08:02.565 --> 08:05.694
Ruth and I decided to buy
the gallery from her parents.

08:05.735 --> 08:08.697
So yeah, that's why I
need the money, okay?

08:11.366 --> 08:13.618
(car starting)

08:13.660 --> 08:16.746
(light guitar music)

08:26.006 --> 08:28.967
(song in foreign language)

08:29.009 --> 08:31.511
Flying dinosaur, 11.

08:31.553 --> 08:32.971
Is it, I don't know,

08:33.013 --> 08:34.764
why don't you ever
drive-a-saurus?

08:37.600 --> 08:39.102
It's never 11 letters.

08:56.453 --> 08:58.204
How about a game of I spy?

08:59.456 --> 09:00.248
(Jack sighing)

09:00.290 --> 09:03.418
I spy with my little eye

09:03.460 --> 09:05.795
something beginning with Q.

09:26.066 --> 09:29.069
(crickets chirping)

09:35.825 --> 09:38.495
(keys clinking)

09:49.923 --> 09:51.007
Let me try.

09:55.345 --> 09:57.514
(banging)

10:03.937 --> 10:05.438
(door creaking)

10:05.480 --> 10:07.774
(slamming)

10:20.620 --> 10:21.621
Oh my god.

10:29.796 --> 10:32.007
I'm gonna wake up in a minute.

10:32.048 --> 10:34.467
Things always look
worse in the dark.

10:38.638 --> 10:40.015
What the fuck is that?

11:10.754 --> 11:12.672
I'll leave you to it.

11:24.351 --> 11:26.895
(somber music)

12:04.057 --> 12:06.226
(sighing)

12:40.260 --> 12:43.013
(birds chirping)

13:12.292 --> 13:15.128
(uplifting music)

13:21.343 --> 13:24.179
(faucet creaking)

13:25.472 --> 13:28.308
(pipes vibrating)

13:29.976 --> 13:32.312
(splashing)

13:38.902 --> 13:41.738
(Jack exclaiming)

14:03.343 --> 14:06.846
(critter snarling)
Huh!?

14:11.184 --> 14:13.436
(rattling)

14:31.871 --> 14:34.332
(Robert sighing)

14:34.374 --> 14:36.418
Pass me the knifey bit.

14:50.724 --> 14:52.142
At least the view's quite good.

14:54.269 --> 14:55.729
That's what you're calling

14:55.770 --> 14:59.524
one of the most spectacular
convergences of nature ever?

14:59.566 --> 15:00.400
The view?

15:01.276 --> 15:02.277
You haven't even looked at it.

15:03.903 --> 15:06.197
Two cypress trees
frame the compositions

15:06.239 --> 15:07.907
subconsciously
propelling the eye

15:07.949 --> 15:10.869
across the negative space
toward the focal point

15:10.910 --> 15:13.747
of the perfectly central villa,

15:13.788 --> 15:16.916
all unified by these magnificent

15:16.958 --> 15:18.626
undulating Tuscany hills.

15:20.337 --> 15:22.756
Late afternoon, remember.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.967
The way the light
hits those windows

15:26.009 --> 15:27.177
takes your breath away.

15:28.094 --> 15:30.138
No, that's the dust doing that.

15:31.598 --> 15:33.767
I mean how could you
let it go like this?

15:36.019 --> 15:37.145
(car honking)

15:37.187 --> 15:39.272
Oh an interruption,
what a shame.

15:39.314 --> 15:40.607
Must be the estate agent.

15:40.648 --> 15:41.649
Damn, she's early.

15:43.818 --> 15:45.278
We'll mark the view as a 10

15:45.320 --> 15:48.281
but the potholes down that
drive are a serious drawback.

15:48.323 --> 15:49.908
I may have whiplash.

15:49.949 --> 15:50.909
One of you is Jack?

15:50.950 --> 15:51.743
I'm Jack.

15:51.785 --> 15:52.577
Kate Lewis.

15:52.619 --> 15:53.745
Jack.

15:53.787 --> 15:54.913
Sorry, I've said that.

15:54.954 --> 15:55.747
Robert.

15:55.789 --> 15:56.748
Hello.

15:56.790 --> 15:59.125
Now, let's see
what we have here.

16:02.170 --> 16:04.172
Not perhaps the best
first impression.

16:04.214 --> 16:06.508
Things can only get better.

16:06.549 --> 16:07.759
Front door?

16:07.801 --> 16:08.635
Ah...

16:20.814 --> 16:22.315
Well I don't even
know what to say

16:22.357 --> 16:24.192
about this whole situation.

16:24.234 --> 16:25.860
Do you know Frank Swine?

16:25.902 --> 16:26.820
Should I?

16:26.861 --> 16:29.656
That is my homage to his style.

16:30.990 --> 16:31.825
You painted it?

16:34.661 --> 16:35.495
I see.

16:47.007 --> 16:50.176
(banging in distance)

16:54.347 --> 16:57.100
(toilet flushing)

17:02.022 --> 17:03.648
There's a large
hole in your roof.

17:03.690 --> 17:06.026
Yes, but it's got great bones.

17:06.067 --> 17:07.234
Don't you think Kate?

17:07.277 --> 17:09.738
Or you prefer Katie?

17:09.779 --> 17:12.240
Just Kate, plain Kate.

17:12.281 --> 17:13.116
A bonny Kate.

17:14.200 --> 17:15.827
And sometimes Kate the cursed,

17:15.868 --> 17:19.079
but Kate, the prettiest
Kate in Christendom.

17:23.251 --> 17:26.628
From the Taming of the,

17:28.048 --> 17:28.882
The shrew?

17:29.966 --> 17:30.800
By Shakespeare.

17:33.303 --> 17:36.848
Do you think we can
make a quick sale, Kate?

17:36.890 --> 17:38.350
Well that depends.

17:38.391 --> 17:39.476
On?

17:39.517 --> 17:41.394
On whether you hope
to make a profit.

17:41.436 --> 17:43.688
Tuscany is a romantic idyll.

17:43.730 --> 17:45.607
It's why all my
clients come here.

17:45.648 --> 17:48.193
If I were to bring them to
this house in this state

17:48.234 --> 17:49.194
they will say to me,

17:49.235 --> 17:52.072
"Kate, you promised me a dream.

17:52.113 --> 17:54.366
"A dream orchestrated by Puccini

17:54.407 --> 17:56.284
"in which my worries
would just float off

17:56.326 --> 17:57.869
"into the infinity pool.

17:57.911 --> 18:01.289
"But instead you have
delivered me a building site

18:01.331 --> 18:04.459
"whose walls seem to have
been painted by Mussolini."

18:06.461 --> 18:07.837
Having said all that,

18:09.172 --> 18:10.715
if you put your backs into it

18:10.757 --> 18:13.468
I don't see why you
couldn't turn this around.

18:13.510 --> 18:16.471
In the plus column, your
plumbing seems to work.

18:16.513 --> 18:17.764
People care about that.

18:19.265 --> 18:21.768
And I like, as you
say, its bones.

18:31.027 --> 18:33.279
(birds chirping)

18:33.321 --> 18:34.781
I wouldn't if I were you.

18:35.824 --> 18:36.991
It's about to rain.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.832
(thunder booming)

18:43.873 --> 18:46.793
(melancholy music)

19:15.321 --> 19:17.490
(banging)

19:20.076 --> 19:22.537
(sighing)

19:22.579 --> 19:25.331
(birds chirping)

19:34.424 --> 19:36.468
I wouldn't go on the
bathroom for a while

19:36.509 --> 19:38.011
if I were you.

19:38.053 --> 19:39.971
There's a large
weasel in the sink.

19:40.013 --> 19:41.848
That's not a euphemism.

19:41.890 --> 19:45.310
No, we'll get what we can
for the house, isn't it?

19:45.352 --> 19:49.314
It'll be fuck all.

19:49.356 --> 19:51.232
But this is
impossible on my own.

19:52.400 --> 19:56.196
Or we could keep it.

19:56.237 --> 19:57.405
Except the weasel.

19:57.447 --> 19:59.324
They're too friendly
for my liking.

19:59.366 --> 20:01.826
Listen, we are going
to sell this house

20:01.868 --> 20:03.078
one way or another.

20:03.119 --> 20:03.995
Get on board with that.

20:04.037 --> 20:04.829
Where are you going?

20:04.871 --> 20:06.206
I've got a gallery to buy.

20:07.207 --> 20:07.999
(door slamming)

20:08.041 --> 20:10.210
(revving)

20:14.631 --> 20:17.008
(phone ringing)

20:17.050 --> 20:18.343
Jack, what do you want?

20:18.385 --> 20:19.469
Ruth.

20:19.511 --> 20:21.513
I just wanted you
to know I'm in Italy

20:21.554 --> 20:24.599
and I persuaded my
dad to sell the house.

20:24.641 --> 20:25.600
So?

20:25.642 --> 20:27.894
So it means I can
buy the gallery.

20:27.936 --> 20:31.022
Sorry, you were
actually being serious.

20:31.064 --> 20:33.733
It's on the market, it's
already been in trust.

20:33.775 --> 20:35.402
You said I had a month.

20:37.904 --> 20:41.408
(melancholy guitar music)

21:08.810 --> 21:11.104
(crashing)

21:18.278 --> 21:20.655
Do you need some help
knocking the others over?

21:22.157 --> 21:24.951
(birds chirping)

21:40.133 --> 21:42.844
(chain clinking)

21:49.809 --> 21:52.312
(light music)

21:55.398 --> 21:57.609
Are you always this busy?

21:57.650 --> 21:58.902
Mondays I'm closed.

22:04.407 --> 22:05.241
So.

22:07.327 --> 22:09.162
Where did you learn
to speak English?

22:11.498 --> 22:12.707
Bugs Bunny.

22:12.749 --> 22:13.667
Huh?

22:13.708 --> 22:14.668
Bugs Bunny.

22:17.003 --> 22:18.546
In Italian schools,
kids are forced

22:18.588 --> 22:20.173
to watch cartoons
for five hours a day

22:20.215 --> 22:21.800
just to learn English.

22:21.841 --> 22:22.717
Really?

22:22.759 --> 22:23.635
Mhmm.

22:23.677 --> 22:24.552
It's the laws.

22:25.428 --> 22:26.304
I had no idea.

22:26.346 --> 22:28.014
That's actually pretty cool.

22:29.182 --> 22:30.975
Of course not.

22:31.017 --> 22:32.644
I lived in England for a year.

22:32.686 --> 22:34.646
I worked in a restaurant there.

22:34.688 --> 22:37.148
And you, you're on holiday?

22:37.190 --> 22:38.566
Oh, no, no, I wish.

22:40.068 --> 22:42.696
I'm actually here to
sell an old family house.

22:42.737 --> 22:44.239
I see, where?

22:44.280 --> 22:46.241
It's out of town towards Pienza.

22:52.622 --> 22:53.581
Oh my gosh.

22:54.541 --> 22:55.709
This is amazing.

22:55.750 --> 22:56.584
I know.

22:57.711 --> 22:59.838
Is your house near
the deserted house?

22:59.879 --> 23:01.381
It's probably the same one.

23:03.466 --> 23:04.759
With the beautiful lake?

23:05.719 --> 23:06.511
Mhmm.

23:06.553 --> 23:08.263
I love that house.

23:08.304 --> 23:09.139
Really?

23:11.391 --> 23:12.225
You wanna buy it?

23:13.351 --> 23:16.438
Well, I can only pay
you with risotto.

23:16.479 --> 23:18.231
How many bowls do
you want for it?

23:21.484 --> 23:23.028
Three should do it.

23:23.069 --> 23:25.488
And I want a nice bottle of red.

23:28.241 --> 23:29.617
You obviously don't understand

23:29.659 --> 23:30.910
how good this risotto is.

23:33.413 --> 23:34.247
Okay, fine.

23:35.081 --> 23:35.915
Two bottles.

23:38.251 --> 23:39.669
They have to be big ones.

23:42.922 --> 23:45.383
I haven't even seen what
it looks like inside.

23:45.425 --> 23:49.262
(coughing) Well, that's
the main selling point.

23:53.767 --> 23:55.226
(light music)

23:55.268 --> 23:58.396
Thank you for the
really lovely food.

23:58.438 --> 23:59.606
(Woman speaks in
foreign language)

23:59.647 --> 24:01.566
You know you're lucky
to have that house.

24:01.608 --> 24:02.901
So pretty.

24:02.942 --> 24:04.235
No.

24:04.277 --> 24:05.445
